column1: 202014;instagram;2019-02-05 14:21:48;FALSE;"’i was a victim too’ – uche jombo speaks on sexual assault in nollywood

column3: made this disclosure in an interview with hiptv while speaking on the widespread allegations of sexual assault on upcoming actresses. “i’ve been in that kind of situation twice during my starting days
column4: ” she said. “i rehearsed for almost two weeks only to come next and find that someone else was reading my role because i declined the request to ‘see me’ (for sex). “i wept seriously
column5: i was hurt but four to five years later
column6: i made it big.” explaining how she survived and maintained her stance at the time
column7: jombo said: “it is personal integrity. in my days
column8: we move on when we’re denied opportunities for refusing to give in to sexual demands. “sometimes
column10: drive and process that matters. what takes some six months to accomplish might take others six years. “are you ready to wait for your time or you just want a shortcut that leads to no long-lasting opportunity? if you want the shortcut
column11: chances are that there are people willing to give it.” jombo said people who engage in such acts should be called out explaining that this would force nollywood recruiters and opportunity givers who indulge in such acts to “be humans again”. .

column1: this.is.everything! had a funny conversation with my mentor recently where our roles reversed. she was feeling demotivated because cis-white-men at work keep asking for her advice and then not taking it. she felt like it was all for nothing and like she wasn’t making any progress.
i told her the fact that she was even in that room being asked for her opinion was progress
column2: that women before us fought for the right just to be in the room. she’s sat there fighting for more so the generations after us can go one step further.
it’s exhausting. self care is important. you feel tired because you’re fighting
column3: you’re not fighting a battle but a full on war. warriors need rest and nourishment. if you feel tired by all of this it’s probably because you’re depleted. it’s ok to step back and take time for yourself.

it sounds dramatic (but!) every pink ladoo contains the battlecry of every woman who has fought for her rights or been denied what she deserves. every pink ladoo is a tiny seed that might germinate inside someone to make them see sense and start abandoning their sexist ways.

column1: as the saying goes “we all stand in the shade of a tree that someone else planted.”

column1: 202069;instagram;2019-02-05 15:00:15;FALSE;"💢خشونت علیه زنان؛ از جای خالی وزیر زن تا ممنوعیت ورود به ورزشگاه ها

✍زهرا علي اكبري 🔸ازسال 2000ميلادي برای تحقق همگامی‌نقش زنان ومردان در اجتماع و حقوق برابر آنها، روز 25نوامبر توسط مجمع عمومی‌سازمان ملل روز جهانی مبارزه با خشونت علیه زنان نامگذاري شده است و هر ساله دولت‌ها، سازمان‌های بین‌‌المللی و سازمان‌های غیر دولتی برای افزایش آگاهی عمومی‌از ابعاد خشونت علیه زنان اين روز بین‌‌المللی را اختصاص به واكاوي چرايي خشونت‌هاي موجود و اقدامات مطلوب براي رفع آنها اختصاص می‌دهند. 🔸خشونت علیه زنان، شکل افراطی و غير قابل درك تبعیض است، که با ویژگی‌های خوی انسانی وحقوقی بشر در تناقض است.طبق گزارش‌هاي جهاني، براساس داده‌های 87 كشور در سال‌های 2005 تا 2016 ميلادي، 19 درصد زنان بین 15 تا 49 ساله گفته‌اند که طی 12 ماهِ گذشته از یک دوست و يا حتي  همسر با آزار و خشونت‌های کلامی، رفتاری، فیزیکی و یا جنسی رو به رو شده‌اند. در ارزيابي‌هاي اين گزارشها  آمده است كه  در موارد شدید، برخی خشونت‌ها حتي  منجر به مرگ شده است. 🔸پژوهش‌هاي حوزه زنان در این خصوص نشان می‌دهد كه در مقایسه با 6 درصد از قربانیان مرد،تقریبا نیمی‌از زنان که قربانی قتل عمدی در سراسر جهان شده‌اند، توسط یک شریک صمیمی‌یا یک عضو خانواده کشته شده‌اند.

یکی دیگر از موارد شدید خشونت علیه زنان، ختنه و سقط جنین است كه خوشبختانه با اطلاع‌رساني و تبيين حقوق زنان این اعمال مضر در دامنه‌ هفده  ساله‌اي (ازسال 2000تا2017) به 24 درصد کاهش یافته واما با این حال، شیوع اين خشونت‌هاي مرگ آور در 30 کشورجهان با داده‌های نمایشی هنوز باقی مانده و محسوس  است. 🔸همه ساله روز 25 نوامبر، سازمان‌ها و انجمن‌ها ونهادهاي فعال در امور زنان، همگان را به «نارنجی کردن جهان» دعوت می‌کنند و با استفاده از رنگ تعیین شده و مشترك در سرتاسر جهان ضمن جلب توجه دیگران به داشتن حق برابری وعدالت، برای نشان دادن آینده روشن‌تر و برابر طلب و بدون خشونت بسترسازي می‌نمايند. 🔸امسال در برابر انواع آزار و اذيت‌هايي كه بر زنان واردمی‌شود، فعاليت‌هاي جهانی بی‌سابقه‌ای صورت گرفته است.میلیون‌ها نفر در پشت پویش #metoo و سایر پویش‌های مشابه قرار گرفته اند، که هر روز آزار و اذیت جنسی و دیگر اشکال خشونت که زنان در همه جا از آنها رنج می‌برند و افسرده شده‌اند را باز گو می‌كنند و به دنبال حذف خشونت علیه زنان،احقاق حقوق و راهکارهای عملی تربرای آن هستند.";;en;#MeToo;;;;;0;;soshyant.arryaeeee;یه شیرپسرایرانی تبارمازندرانیم;;0;False;4;0;0;78;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/8e958413d654869255239b2a74accf95/5C7F94DE/t51.2885-15/e35/50762762_2458490147554609_5051940677608309726_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"💢خشونت علیه زنان؛ از جای خالی وزیر زن تا ممنوعیت ورود به ورزشگاه ها

✍زهرا علي اكبري 🔸ازسال 2000ميلادي برای تحقق همگامی‌نقش زنان ومردان در اجتماع و حقوق برابر آنها، روز 25نوامبر توسط مجمع عمومی‌سازمان ملل روز جهانی مبارزه با خشونت علیه زنان نامگذاري شده است و هر ساله دولت‌ها، سازمان‌های بین‌‌المللی و سازمان‌های غیر دولتی برای افزایش آگاهی عمومی‌از ابعاد خشونت علیه زنان اين روز بین‌‌المللی را اختصاص به واكاوي چرايي خشونت‌هاي موجود و اقدامات مطلوب براي رفع آنها اختصاص می‌دهند. 🔸خشونت علیه زنان، شکل افراطی و غير قابل درك تبعیض است، که با ویژگی‌های خوی انسانی وحقوقی بشر در تناقض است.طبق گزارش‌هاي جهاني، براساس داده‌های 87 كشور در سال‌های 2005 تا 2016 ميلادي، 19 درصد زنان بین 15 تا 49 ساله گفته‌اند که طی 12 ماهِ گذشته از یک دوست و يا حتي  همسر با آزار و خشونت‌های کلامی، رفتاری، فیزیکی و یا جنسی رو به رو شده‌اند. در ارزيابي‌هاي اين گزارشها  آمده است كه  در موارد شدید، برخی خشونت‌ها حتي  منجر به مرگ شده است. 🔸پژوهش‌هاي حوزه زنان در این خصوص نشان می‌دهد كه در مقایسه با 6 درصد از قربانیان مرد،تقریبا نیمی‌از زنان که قربانی قتل عمدی در سراسر جهان شده‌اند، توسط یک شریک صمیمی‌یا یک عضو خانواده کشته شده‌اند.

یکی دیگر از موارد شدید خشونت علیه زنان، ختنه و سقط جنین است كه خوشبختانه با اطلاع‌رساني و تبيين حقوق زنان این اعمال مضر در دامنه‌ هفده  ساله‌اي (ازسال 2000تا2017) به 24 درصد کاهش یافته واما با این حال، شیوع اين خشونت‌هاي مرگ آور در 30 کشورجهان با داده‌های نمایشی هنوز باقی مانده و محسوس  است. 🔸همه ساله روز 25 نوامبر، سازمان‌ها و انجمن‌ها ونهادهاي فعال در امور زنان، همگان را به «نارنجی کردن جهان» دعوت می‌کنند و با استفاده از رنگ تعیین شده و مشترك در سرتاسر جهان ضمن جلب توجه دیگران به داشتن حق برابری وعدالت، برای نشان دادن آینده روشن‌تر و برابر طلب و بدون خشونت بسترسازي می‌نمايند. 🔸امسال در برابر انواع آزار و اذيت‌هايي كه بر زنان واردمی‌شود، فعاليت‌هاي جهانی بی‌سابقه‌ای صورت گرفته است.میلیون‌ها نفر در پشت پویش #metoo و سایر پویش‌های مشابه قرار گرفته اند، که هر روز آزار و اذیت جنسی و دیگر اشکال خشونت که زنان در همه جا از آنها رنج می‌برند و افسرده شده‌اند را باز گو می‌كنند و به دنبال حذف خشونت علیه زنان،احقاق حقوق و راهکارهای عملی تربرای آن هستند.";"💢خشونت علیه زنان؛ از جای خالی وزیر زن تا ممنوعیت ورود به ورزشگاه ها

حال، شیوع اين خشونت‌هاي مرگ آور در 30 کشورجهان با داده‌های نمایشی هنوز باقی مانده و محسوس  است. 🔸همه ساله روز 25 نوامبر، سازمان‌ها و انجمن‌ها ونهادهاي فعال در امور زنان، همگان را به «نارنجی کردن جهان» دعوت می‌کنند و با استفاده از رنگ تعیین شده و مشترك در سرتاسر جهان ضمن جلب توجه دیگران به داشتن حق برابری وعدالت، برای نشان دادن آینده روشن‌تر و برابر طلب و بدون خشونت بسترسازي می‌نمايند. 🔸امسال در برابر انواع آزار و اذيت‌هايي كه بر زنان واردمی‌شود، فعاليت‌هاي جهانی بی‌سابقه‌ای صورت گرفته است.میلیون‌ها نفر در پشت پویش  و سایر پویش‌های مشابه قرار گرفته اند، که هر روز آزار و اذیت جنسی و دیگر اشکال خشونت که زنان در همه جا از آنها رنج می‌برند و افسرده شده‌اند را باز گو می‌كنند و به دنبال حذف خشونت علیه زنان،احقاق حقوق و راهکارهای عملی تربرای آن هستند.";💢خشونت علیه زنان؛ از جای خالی وزیر زن تا با این حال، شیوع اين خشونت‌هاي مرگ آور در 30 کشورجهان با داده‌های نمایشی هنوز باقی مانده و محسوس است . 🔸همه ساله روز 25 نوامبر، سازمان‌ها و انجمن‌ها ونهادهاي فعال در امور زنان، همگان را به « نارنجی کردن جهان » دعوت می‌کنند و با استفاده از رنگ تعیین شده و مشترك در سرتاسر جهان ضمن جلب توجه دیگران به داشتن حق برابری وعدالت، برای نشان دادن آینده روشن‌تر و برابر طلب و بدون خشونت بسترسازي می‌نمايند . 🔸امسال در برابر انواع آزار و اذيت‌هايي كه بر زنان واردمی‌شود، فعاليت‌هاي جهانی بی‌سابقه‌ای صورت گرفته است.میلیون‌ها نفر در پشت پویش و سایر پویش‌های مشابه قرار گرفته اند، که هر روز آزار و اذیت جنسی و دیگر اشکال خشونت که زنان در همه جا از آنها رنج می‌برند و افسرده شده‌اند را باز گو می‌كنند و به دنبال حذف خشونت علیه زنان،احقاق حقوق و راهکارهای عملی تربرای آن هستند .

column2: we had a group of 4 girls famous by the name 'topi band'. there was a guy
column3: who had proposed me & one of my friends on facebook
column4: but we rejected. one morning as we 4 met in class each person told the other that they recieved a very negative
column5: sexual message from that guy. unable to harass me with messages
column6: he commented sexual & physical comments on the posts of mine which were public. we told this to a teacher of ours. to which she told us to unfriend him
column7: but he wasn't even in our friend list in the first place. i found it necessary to show it to my mother
column8: when i did show her the comments she said that it was so bad that i wouldn't have been able to understand them at that age. she phoned my class teacher & complained
column9: to which he said that he is also a kid & a student.?we can't destroy his life. he told my mom to deactivate facebook accounts of all of us instead. no proper action was taken
column10: but we didn't stop doing & being what we wanted to. after a few months a case happened in another branch of my school after which we were called to sessions in which we were told to complain even if someone talks with us in an inappropriate manner
column12: no actions are taken until something bad happens. that guy was resticated from school as he didn't come to school frequently for long durations. he was also not allowed to appear in boards due to the same reason. all i want to convey from the incident is
column13: we need to stop such harassers instead of the victims to stop harassment cases
column14: we shouldn't wait for something bad to happen. that's what my mother told me in that moment
column15: that's what i will carry with me always. if i'm not wrong

column1: 202099;instagram;2019-02-05 15:36:16;FALSE;"what if women weren't objects of desire but desire itself? how can sensual power be feminist power?  feminism used to be about being strong like a man. and - quite rightly - having the right to have everything a man has a right to. but what if the feminine has a gift
column3: that men would just die for?  a manifesting power  so sensual and pleasurable that it is secretly the most powerful thing in our world? in the age of #metoo and the #timesup movement
column4: women can be in danger of abandoning their right to be straight up sacred sexual beings. we can hide our juicy light in the hopes of protecting it - and it not being taken from us without permission. or in fear of it being shamed by the patriarchy for being ""too sexy."" this dieing that the patriarchy feels when it knows it is not the feminine is the same death that the feminine fears around showing her true power. and our sensual power isn't even just for men or partners. it can be leaned into as a magical resource for ourselves. alas
column6: we are being had! time is well and truly up! february is a key month where we can remember freyja the norse goddess of erotic love. she used to be celebrated on february 14th. and then the church made up a saint and changed this date to valentine's day. sigh. (if you'd like to read more about when pre-patriarchy this day was known as freyja's day
column7: please read my pieces on @the_numinous - which you can find links to in my bio.) in short
column8: we are taking this day the fuck back! i held a beautiful freyja's day goddess circle in nyc @thealchemistskitchen last year - and this year i am thrilled to be holding one in london on february 13th
column9: on the eve of freyja's day @slc_london . there'll be storytelling

column20: @slc_london;;;;0;;lateralhaze;Lucy North;;0;False;24;0;0;136;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/025944de26d4e67fa2b3b1f181f69481/5D21B516/t51.2885-15/e15/50534849_284741742213203_2512626738805247275_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"what if women weren't objects of desire but desire itself? how can sensual power be feminist power?  feminism used to be about being strong like a man. and - quite rightly - having the right to have everything a man has a right to. but what if the feminine has a gift
column22: that men would just die for?  a manifesting power  so sensual and pleasurable that it is secretly the most powerful thing in our world? in the age of #metoo and the #timesup movement
column23: women can be in danger of abandoning their right to be straight up sacred sexual beings. we can hide our juicy light in the hopes of protecting it - and it not being taken from us without permission. or in fear of it being shamed by the patriarchy for being ""too sexy."" this dieing that the patriarchy feels when it knows it is not the feminine is the same death that the feminine fears around showing her true power. and our sensual power is not even just for men or partners. it can be leaned into as a magical resource for ourselves. alas
column25: we are being had! time is well and truly up! february is a key month where we can remember freyja the norse goddess of erotic love. she used to be celebrated on february 14th. and then the church made up a saint and changed this date to valentine's day. sigh. (if you'd like to read more about when pre-patriarchy this day was known as freyja's day

column1: 202257;instagram;2019-02-05 17:49:52;FALSE;"what our society needs is a culture of human interaction that is based on consent.
what our society needs is a culture of relation and touch that isn´t endangering.
we need tools that enable us to create this culture. tools to differentiate between connection and crossing boundaries

column4: intimacy and sexuality are expressed authentically

column2: where every being is able to get in respectful connection and touch with others.

column1: the wheel of consent by dr. betty martin is one of these tools. it´s a communication tool that supports you in experiencing a clear physical encounter and touch.
consent and self-determination play a fundamental part in bodywork and in the areas of conscious sexuality (like tantra e.g.)
column2: as it is the case in my workshops and individual bodywork.

column1: because it is such an important issue many of my clients come to me to learn more about their own needs and boundaries. i am very aware of my responsibility as a trainer and bodyworker. and that´s the reason why i decided to do some further training with dr. betty martin. in april 2019 i will participate at the wheel of consent professionals training as part of the workstudy team. (workstudy means i am learning and supporting betty martin and her team on-site.) “we don't have to do all of it alone. we were never meant to.”
to change the culture of relation and touch in our society
column2: everyone has to do their part.

column1: i want to share my knowledge and tools from my experience as a bodyworker and workshop facilitator
column2: from the wheel of consent professionals training
column3: the urban tantra professionals training (barbara carrellas) and trainings with the school of erotic mysteries uk. a powerful mix.

column2: i have some free offers for all of you
column3: who need and want it (regardless of a donation): https://www.gofundme.com/wheel-of-consent-training

202259;instagram;2019-02-05 17:50:13;TRUE;;#repost @behavebrave with @get_repost
as a girl you start experiencing physical and verbal assault around the age of 11. this normalises it
column2: it becomes a part of every day life. wake up
column5: tolerate someone making you feel uncomfortable because you have a vagina
column6: have a cup of tea or two. i’ve realised more and more

column1: i live in salem with my husband and dog and am so lucky to be married to my best friend. we relocated here a few years ago from northern california
column2: and love oregon. we love exploring the outdoors; hiking

empowered and lucky to have joined this amazing group of women and the 2019 vagina monologues cast! i saw this show around 2003 for the first time. it allowed me to address my recent (at that time) abuse
column3: and to start my healing process. for me
column4: part of the honor of performing these stories is that i want to help someone heal & release the way i did. i want to give people a voice that do not have one. i want to be a part of starting the uncomfortable/difficult conversations we need to have. i feel that the vagina monologues and other similar platforms are what helped to start the #metoo movement
column5: looong before it had a name. i want to help keep that motion going. i am honored that i get to be part of something so powerful and healing and to perform for my first time ever!

column1: 202399;instagram;2019-02-05 20:25:31;FALSE;"🏴black history👂🏾▶️🔊🔊 ""my boss called me a n*gger & i quit!... but the babies bellies are empty & you can see it 👀...my manhood is slowly being destroyed & now the love we had for each other is being destroyed"" -baldwin

column2: world renowned black author/novelist #jamesbaldwin has a candid conversation with legendary poet/activist #nikkigiovanni ...watch as baldwin
column4: painstakingly breaks down the nuances of the plight facing the male afrikan in an #economic system that was not designed for him; yet he still has to find a way to navigate as to both keep his dignity as a man & provide for his family...

column1: 👉🏾this conversation is profound in that it still remains relevant 46yrs later!!..as #america makes advances & moves forward in technology and social standards
column2: the ugly core  functionality has not changed thus creating a quasi-reality  of ""progress""...today in 2019 the idea of a black alpha-male is being discarded
column3: frowned upon and even labeled as ""toxic""
column4: as the #metoo movement & #imwithher movement have garnered more attention & notoriety over the last few years due to high profile sex crimes cases such as #billcosby (who to date has been the only person sent to prison!)...the #blackwoman has been figuratively & literally screaming to the black man that she has it harder than him
column5: and is now showing the world she is a force to be reckoned with...meanwhile #blackmen are literally confused as to what being a real man looks like & what that calls for
column6: as the images & legacies of their heroes and fathers and their inner-social norms and acts of consideration for their former #fairersex are being ripped apart...what prism are we viewing the world thru? .. how is this going to help us in the long run if we dont have #unity #empathy amongst us as black people???🤔❤🖤💚 #legitimatequestions #stepintothelight #refineculture .

column1: i recently opened pandoras box and shared i’ve been sexually abused 8 years ago
column2: so of course i am going to react and feel like a victim again and all the feelings related to the abuse.
so that i dont stand alone in this and hopefully it will help others who’ve had similar experiences and to recognize how brave it is when we dare to open old wounds
column3: because that’s what will make them heal. let’s stick together and keep on sharing. that’s how we’ll work our way through it. feel free to pm me if you feel like sharing.

column3: but it’s never too late to speak up!!!)

column3: involves no meal planning or gym membership and you’ll wake each day feeling amazing. it’s called the sleep diet. ⁣

column1: did you know 1 out of 3 of us are getting less than 6 hours of sleep? we’re getting less each year. what’s to blame? stress? netflix? smartphones? probably all. 😬 if you want to lose weight
column2: you might give the sleep diet a try. ⁣

column1: here’s what 7.5 - 8 hours a night will do for you: ⁣
😴you’ll lose more fat. dieters who got less than 7 hours of sleep experienced 55% less fat loss compared to those who got 7 hrs or more. more sleep = more fat loss
😴you’ll have better blood sugar control. sleep deprivation decreases insulin sensitivity
column2: which leads to increased fat storage. ⁣
that’s a stretch. but when you get enough sleep
column3: your hunger hormones work in your favor & studies show your brain is less resistant to tempting foods. ⁣🍩

column1: 😴your gym time will be worth it. getting enough sleep optimizes muscle synthesis. ⁣
moral of the story. sleep rules. i’m a parent
column3: but i also think it comes down to priorities. you deserve everything the sleep diet offers

column1: i'm showing work from this series in a show that opens on saturday @catalystgallery it was difficult for me to get it together to get this work finished and submitted on time. i had a major block to returning to it as it has become linked to something that happened to me 2 months ago.  a few hours after starting this series i was sexually assaulted on the street. it happened near my apartment. the guy jumped me from behind
column2: reaching between my legs and grabbing me. i was bleeding at the time and he grabbed me by my pad. this made it feel all the more violating. i was able to spin around and began punching him in the kidneys as best i could while he had me struggling in a bear hug. he continuined to grab at me all over. it was freezing rain out and i was hampered by my big coat. the attack did not stop until he saw some people round the corner. (they did nothing to help me btw) once i was free i screamed after him and shoved him down the street as he retreated. i was spitting with rage. i wasn't physically hurt too bad
column3: sore neck and shoulders.  broken nails and scraped hands. although some of this also happened when i came home and beat up the walls. even with the adrenaline pumping it was not lost on me that the attack started literally by being grabbed by the pussy.  this wasn't the worst sexual assault i've ever experienced but it had been awhile. at this point in my life i am more in touch with my emotions so i really had to deal with them in the aftermath. i kept feeling like i was overreacting but i realized this time i wasn't partying the pain away like i had in the past. i was feeling it all. and i was finally processing some of that old stuff along with it. which was really hard. i was fortunate to be able to go to emdr therapy which helped to process it and rid my body of some of the hypervigilence. i wasn't ready to talk about it publicly until i worked through some of this but i think it's important to. so here i am-moving ahead with this series and sharing with you all. #stopmen #metoo (again) #fucktrump #punchhiminthekidneys #enraged . . . . .

column1: 202480;instagram;2019-02-05 22:04:57;FALSE;"what it’s like to love a wild woman by farah ayaad.  to be wild means to be skin free
column2: heart free and soul free. to be wild means to be led by the heart. and what i mean by the heart is the passion that ignites life and purpose in someone’s being. a wild woman is neither good nor bad; she is right in the middle
column3: playfully creating her own sense of balance.

column2: and she is hard to find. she is chaotic
column3: if not chaos itself. a wild woman is full of surprises and is always up to some kind of adventure. she has love for everyone
column4: and it’s that kind of love that comes with no conditions

column1: a wild woman is scary because she is a dream you have given-up on
column2: a dream you’ve never thought would come true after all the broken promises
there she is that wild woman! she is standing right in-front of you
column3: looking back at you with such grace yet power in her eyes that leaves you a clueless little kid all over again.

column1: she fucks you right. she knows your weak spot but she never uses it against you unless she has her mind set on blowing yours. she cares about what excites you and she intentionally does what terrifies you. she is open-minded about trying new things and open to have the most honest conversations you have ever had. giving is a natural instinct of hers: the more she gives

a wild woman is gentle and rough; she likes romance just as much as she likes kinky stuff. she ignites desire in your heart and body by stimulating your mind. she can read what you are thinking like she’s reading lines from her favorite book.
she drives you crazy because as much as you try to put your guard up
column2: as much as you try to say no to her
column3: as much as you try to keep her on some sort of an edge
column4: she has you flying in the sky one moment and on the ground the next one.

column1: her kisses catch your breath away and they make you feel something you haven’t felt in a while. you just cannot keep-up
she’s a fighter. a wild woman does not give it to you on a silver platter. she calls you out on your shit. she is hard on you because she sees potential in you

column1: 202508;instagram;2019-02-05 22:42:14;FALSE;"a spiritual connection is deeper than any religious connection. because i’m spiritually connected to the universe i’m able to tap into any religion and be apart of the essence of higher power. however you call it
column2: i call it faith in divine intuition. ⠀

column1: the divine spoke to me and told me while i was in thailand to go and pray. get on your knees and bow your head
column2: humble yourself and wait for silence to begin. i couldn’t ignore what i heard and felt. the first temple i went to was where the first monk of buddhism was built. i swear i saw the monk statue smile at me and the statue of the elephants prance as i walked closer. to me that was confirmation i was in the right place. so i lit the incense watched the smoke rise and whispered into the smoke please let my soul be heard. i got on my knees and waited for everyone’s voices to quiet down and for it to just be me and the great essence. i asked for my soul to be heard and for my mind and heart to not interfere. i prayed for myself. as i finished
column3: i heard a voice like my mothers tell me i was heard and it thanked me. how magical this experience was. the second temple i went to was a ruined temple where thailand had one of its most destructive wars. i prayed to the sleeping buddha. i asked for my heart and soul to be heard. i pray for the people of america. because that’s the only place i know to be home. it’s not safe and we are not free. and there is no peace. i pray for the day everyone is “woke” and decides to take action. i pray that everyone loves themselves and sees themselves as the other. love. then we will be unified. see the way to this through me! and she told me i was heard and as she thanked me i thanked her. ⠀

column1: حُكم على الممثل lee myung haeng بالسجن لمدة سنة بعد ظاهرة me too
كان الممثل لي ميونغ هاينغ، الذي كان في فبراير عام 2018 أول ممثل مسرحي متهم في ظاهرة metoo الكورية، قد حُكم عليه بالسجن لمدة ثمانية أشهر بتهمة التحرش الجنسي.
كما أمر القاضي وي سو هيون، الذي ترأس القضية، الممثل بإكمال دورة لمدة 40 ساعة بشأن العنف الجنسي وحظر على الممثل الحصول على عمل في أي مؤسسة معنية بالشباب لمدة ثلاث سنوات.
ﻗﺎل اﻟﻘﺎﺿﻲ: “ﻟﻢ ﻳﺘﻤﻜﻦ اﻟﻤﺪﻋﻰ ﻋﻠﻴﻪ ﻣﻦ اﻟﺘﻮﺻﻞ إﻟﻰ اﺗﻔﺎق ﻣﻊ اﻟﻤﺪﻋﻲ، وﺛﻤﺔ ﺧﻄﺮ ﺑﺎرﺗﻜﺎب ﻣﺨﺎﻟﻔﺔ، لقد أخذت بعين الاعتبار أن المدعى عليه ليس لديه إدانة سابقة من نفس النوع وأنه اعترف بجريمته”
وقالت المدعية عليها في القضية في مقابلة مع سيئول شينمون: “لقد حققت ذلك من خلال المحاكمة لأنني مصممة على ألا أعيش كضحية، من الآن فصاعدًا، أريد أن أعود إلى نفسي كعضوة إنتاج مسرحي وامرأة “

وواصلت حديثها عن الواقع المرير المتمثل في توجيه مثل هذا الاتهام: “إذا لم يكن المهاجم مشهوراً أو لم يتم الكشف عن اسم الضحية الحقيقي، فإن الحقيقة هي أنك لن تحصل على نفس القدر من الاهتمام أو الدعم، كنت أتوقع أن تكون قضيتي منخفضة”

وقالت إن الطريقة الوحيدة للعودة إلى نفسها هي فرض العدالة، وكشفت عن أن خيارها أن تظل مجهولة الهوية هي حماية نفسها من ردة الفعل العنيف وقالت: “إن المحكمة أقرت بجرائم [لي ميونغ هاينغ] وحكمت عليه بالسجن تعني الكثير، لقد حصل ضحايا آخرون على الشجاعة والقوة في هذا الحكم”
وقد أضاف مخطط إنتاجي يدعم فيه المدعية: “إن التدريب في مسرح يغطي هذه الأنواع من الحالات هو السبب وراء انتشار العنف الجنسي في الصناعة إلى هذا الحد”

بعد أن اتهم لي ميونغ هاينغ بالتحرش الجنسي في فبراير من العام الماضي، نشر اعتذارًا على صفحته الرسمية على موقع فيس بوك على الإنترنت، واستقال من مسرحية “قبلة امرأة العنكبوت” التي كان يمثل بها في ذلك الوقت.

column1: almost 2 years ago i began semi regularly modelling when i realized i had lost 120 pounds and a relationship came to very bitter end. i needed something to see my own strength my own beauty both inside and out. i needed to see what everyone else saw in me that i had forgetten. i had to remember that love ❤️ real love stemmed from me first not putting myself last. i stand again at a similar situation not because i gave up all of me but because i stood up for me and other women. this won’t stop my faith in the good in people nor will i hide under a rock or seek to play victim. what i will do is march forward with my truth in my pocket and do better. show the strength in me so that others will stand up. show my kids what it means to be strong #metoo #selfportrait #shareyourtruth #modelingbio #backstory #whatdrivesme #beautyinstrength";;en;#metoo

202598;instagram;2019-02-06 00:14:07;FALSE;perempuan butuh syariat islam

column3: menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

column1: pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks
column2: “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua
column4: merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga
column6: dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata
column8: rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan
column9: “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual
column10: bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya

column1: i wrote a song about consent and assault from an attacker’s perspective. you hear so many arguments against victims that somehow still hold ground today. “what was she wearing?” “well you shouldn’t dress that way if you don’t want that kind of attention”. i decided to take another approach to point out how disturbing the common arguments really are. i hope this gives some perspective to people who just don’t get it. there is no excuse. #nomeansno #metoo #metoomovement .. .

column2: the latest sign that there is no end in sight to the #catholicchurch’s abuse crisis — and that it now has a reckoning from the #metoo movement.

column1: francis admitted to the problem for the first time in public during a news conference while returning to #rome from the #unitedarabemirates. the acknowledgment comes just two weeks before he hosts an unprecedented gathering of bishops to craft a global response to the scandal of priestly predators who target children and the superiors who covered up the crimes.
francis was asked about priests who target adult women — the religious sisters who are the backbone of the catholic church’s education
column2: health care and social service ministries around the globe — and whether the holy see might consider a similar universal approach to combat that issue. “it’s not that everyone does this
column3: but there have been priests and bishops who have
column4: ” francis told reporters. “and i think that it’s continuing because it’s not like once you realize it that it stops. it continues. and for some time we’ve been working on it.” “should we do something more? yes. is there the will? yes. but it’s a path that we have already begun

202696;instagram;2019-02-06 02:42:35;FALSE;• @time democratic #women are wearing white clothing to make a coordinated #fashion statement around president #trump's state of the union address in washington, d.c., on feb. 5. borrowing from the color used by the early 20th century movement to recognize women’s right to vote, the house democratic women’s working group invited lawmakers to wear white as a sign of #solidarity. in this photograph, @speakerpelosi stands with democratic house members during a photo-op that recognized suffragettes. last year, the group asked both male and female members of congress to wear black to the #sotu to show solidarity with the #metoo and time’s up movements. read more at the link in bio. photograph by joshua roberts (@jprpix)—@reuters;;en;#women

column1: #motivationmonday this ones for those who #supportsurvivors out there. step 1) believe them. step 2) just listen step 3) get help if needed. 4) walk with and love them unconditionally. repeat. this sequence may look different depending on the survivors needs/wants throughout their journey at any given moment and at times the survivor may not know what they want/need in any given moment as trauma is often very complex and different for each survivor. sometimes you just being there or a call/text/message/email away is all they need. no advice
column2: just love. meet them where they are at and love. do something fun and love. contribute to self-care routine and love. get basic needs met (food/drink/coffee) and love. validate and love. just listen and love. love above all else. #metoo #survivorsupport #selfcare #justlisten #neveralone #throughitall #healing #love ☂️💜🎆🌞";en;#Repost

bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

column1: 202876;instagram;2019-02-06 07:07:46;FALSE;"this week marks sexual abuse and sexual violence awareness week 2019. in may
column2: i am running the #leedshalfmarathon to #fundraise for my local rape crisis service
column4: please donate!). one of the reasons i am doing this is to #raiseawareness of what actually makes something a rape or sexual assault. in 2019
column5: it is heartbreaking to think this even needs further clarity
column6: but the recent survey statistics for the uk from december 2018 are haunting:

column1: * a third of people think it isn’t usually rape if a woman is pressured into having sex but there is no physical violence
* a third of men think if a woman has flirted on a date it generally wouldn’t count as rape
column2: even if she hasn’t explicitly consented to sex (compared with a fifth of women)

column1: * a third of men also believe a woman can’t change her mind after sex has started
* a quarter of people think that sex without consent in long-term relationships is usually not rape.
* ‘stealthing’: 40% think it is never or usually not rape to remove a condom without a partner’s consent
these attitudes influence the level of professional and informal support women receive if they choose to share their stories
column2: as well as being horrendously revictimising. it’s scary to think where survivors would be without services like sarsvl where they are always believed and understood.

202915;instagram;2019-02-06 08:21:56;FALSE;my favorite part of every fashion show is the end when they do the “grand parade.” years ago my friend faye chen ran the seamstresses for marc jacobs & asked me if i’d like to be a volunteer “changer” for his show. “sure
column2: but what’ll i have to do?” “you know how during a show you see the same model come out in a different outfit in 2 minutes & you don’t know how she can change so quickly?” “yeah...?” “well
column3: that’s what changers do. you have to rip the clothes off the models as quickly as possible. they’ll just raise their hands and you rip off the garments. don’t worry about damaging them-i can fix that. we just want them undressed as quickly as possible. and you’re not dressing them-just undressing them. ok?” “um...yeah.” “oh
column4: i forgot-we don’t usually use undergarments because they tend to roll & show lines & marc hates that. so most of the models will be totally naked underneath. that’s not going to bother you
column7: i think i’ll be fine with that”. “oh
column8: one last thing. last year we had some problems with a few of the changers staring at the models & making them feel uncomfortable. so just look like you don’t care
column9: or pretend you’re gay. you can do that for me
column11: i can certainly be gay for one night!” this was 15 years before the metoo movement. well
column12: what happened? 2 days before the show
column13: faye calls me & cancels. apparently marc decided to hire professional changers
column16: was one of the saddest moments of my life. but to make up
column17: faye gave me tickets to the after party

column50: that’s what changers do. you have to rip the clothes off the models as quickly as possible. they’ll just raise their hands and you rip off the garments. don’t worry about damaging them-i can fix that. we just want them undressed as quickly as possible. and you’re not dressing them-just undressing them. ok?” “um...yeah.” “oh
column51: i forgot-we don’t usually use undergarments because they tend to roll & show lines & marc hates that. so most of the models will be totally naked underneath. that’s not going to bother you
column54: i think i’ll be fine with that”. “oh
column55: one last thing. last year we had some problems with a few of the changers staring at the models & making them feel uncomfoable. so just look like you don’t care
column56: or pretend you’re gay. you can do that for me
column58: i can ceainly be gay for one night!” this was 15 years before the metoo movement. well
column59: what happened? 2 days before the show
column60: faye calls me & cancels. apparently marc decided to hire professional changers
column63: was one of the saddest moments of my life. but to make up
column64: faye gave me tickets to the after pay

column1: 202960;instagram;2019-02-06 10:41:46;FALSE;"i just came across another one of those snake oil sales pitches about turning your life around for success in 90days. those people can make you feel like an under achiever. don't listen to them. its taken me 4 years to be satisfied enough with my personal goals to print them out. i went to my therapist in the uk for the first time in 5 years. he's reviewing my old notes  and says ""you said then nigeria brutalized you. hows being back in nigeria going for you?"" i had to smile. i said that? because i'm loving nigeria and my life in nigeria  right now. i gave him a noble reason for staying. something about opportunity to make a difference. now that's change. now that's a story. it didn't happen in 90 days. i went from beaten and broken to enthusiastic and happy. and it took 5 years putting one foot in front of the other. one day at a time. and putting my well being before everything else. i misspent my youth riding myself worse than any slave master. demanding more and more and better and better from myself and ignoring my well being.  don't let the self help gurus make you feel bad. just keep putting one foot in front of the other. its not a destination. its a journey. they're no winners or losers.  peace
